text: The RC gets a lot of shit thrown their way but the idea that they don’t understand competitive gameplay is next-level BS
Is the issue that the don’t understand the gameplay or that they actively and vocally dislike the cEDH mentality?
That they don’t*
I’ve never once questioned Sheldon’s ability to play Magic at a high level but I have seen him blatantly say cEDH doesn’t follow the social contract HE envisions for the format.

Which... is fine.
To paraphrase their document, they don’t want to steer EDH to be a “competitive entity.”

Sure but there’s a group of people that enjoy it. From what I’ve seen, they don’t approve of cEDH splitting into its own thing but they also don’t want to steer the format with them in mind. That, to me, says they just don’t want cEDH to exist and that’s not fair.
Rachel on the CAG already means they’re overrepresented tenfold

It’s one thing to have those opinions and visions for your playgroup but being the governing body of a format across so many groups means you should consider and fairly weigh opinions you may not personally agree with.

I think I get super attached because I turn to MTG in general to deal with things. The days I sit down and write articles are normally the days I have something bothering me or am dealing with depression. I push it all away and bring up 20 tabs of cards, EDHREC pages, Scryfall searches, deck lists, etc. and just read and think and eventually I'm not as upset or at least not feeling it at that moment.

I used to do the same thing with writing. A lot of my depression stints turn into insomnia and I used to stay awake and just write short stories or chapters or even just character bios. But writing is kind of a solo hobby. I can share stuff and if people are interested, have someone to talk about it, but MTG already has an audience, so I just share my thoughts online and find people who want to talk
See there you go
Thats what you want out of it
Because the thing I go to in order to cope with depression sometimes depresses me? :stuck_out_tongue:
Haha yeah not trying to make light of the situation or make it sound easy. But i dont work on edhrec because of something i want from edh, its more a creative outlet for me when i feel stuck at work
My point is maybe its not about edh, its more about coping? Not sure
I think all these angry people on twitter are trying to get too much out of edh itself
Also, and this may be controversial, people like being offended about things.
TAKE THAT BACK.
If you're offended, that means you're right.
I'm not sure it's "I like being offended" as much as "I think I'm right and I'm not looking for people to disagree with me"
Everyone knows best because everyone is the smartest person in the room
In their own minds
Twitter might be designed as an outlet for people thinking they know something
Well I missed some stuff didn’t I?
I think it's multiple sides of the same coin.
They may not be looking to ruffle feathers, but when they're disagreed with, immediate response is get angry or offended.
People tie too much of their own identity to their expressed opinions and ideas about an ostensibly leisure activity.
So when someone disagrees, they feel personally attacked and the fight/flight mechanism kicks in.
Yeah, that's true
I'm guilty of that a bunch of times
I will say I think I do a better job than most of recognizing it and trying to resist the reflex
Not perfect every time, obviously, but I've calmed myself down before replying to tons of messages
